statement:
Let $f:\mathbb{R}^+\rightarrow \mathbb{R^+}$ be a function with the
following properties:

1.  $\log f(x)$ is a convex function (i.e. $f$ is logarithmically
    convex);

2.  $f(x+1) = xf(x)$ for all $x>0$;

3.  $f(1)=1.$

Then $f(x)=\Gamma(x)$ for all $x>0$.\
That is, the only function satisfying those properties is the gamma
function (restricted to the positive reals.)
